  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">ERFS 2019 Cyclone Idai-Emergency Flood Response In Chikwawa</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1,000 highly vulnerable households have access to cash to meet their immediate needs(food and shelter). for about two months 
450 pregnant and lactating women and 750 children aged 6 months to 5 years have received specialised nutritious foods to prevent undernutrition, morbidity and mortality</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">the response will involve the following
1.Cash Transfer: Christian Aid will provide multi-purpose cash support to 1,000 highly vulnerable flood-affected households. Each household will receive approx. &#x20AC;23 per month for two months, in two disbursements.
2.  Nutritious Food Distribution: Christian Aid will provide specialised nutritious foods to 450 pregnant and lactating women and 750 children aged between 6 months and 5 years</narrative>
  </description>
